cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.NE 

The paper discusses reinforcement learning from a computer science perspective, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses issues related to decision-making and control, which are relevant to robotics and control systems, making cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks and other artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of empirical models and learning from delayed reinforcement, which are relevant to neural networks and other computational models, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category as well.
